  "doc_id": "54063",
  "text": "Active tuberculosis is primarily a disease of the lung, but it can progress to a generalized inflammatory disease. Mycobacterium tuberculosis (MTB) is a peculiar pathogen, because it resides within a phagosome-like compartment of host macrophages during infection, where it can suppress inflammasome activation [CITATION_1] . However, MTB has the ability to activate the NLRP3 inflammasome, depending on the expression of a functional protein secretion system (ESX-1). (17) The pathways that lead to inflammasome activation in this pathogen are not completely understood, but the export of ESAT-6 (early secreted antigenic target, 6 kDa, a family of small proteins secreted by MTB) via ESX-1 appears to be of critical importance [CITATION_2] .",
